description:
The Little Wanderer and Victory for Venus are reprinted stories from Space Adventures #35, and Space Adventures #37

The Little Wanderer

Billy Goslin the son of Gunner Goslin, (Captain Atom's/Allen Adam) best friend has the power to separate himself while he is sleeping into two persons. One stays asleep while the other is awake. In these incidents he plays with a giant alien bird called Loga that flies in space. It is not known if it is the bird that gives him the power or does it come from Billy himself.

At first no one believes Billy when they tells them about his adventures until one day Billy doesn't wake up. For two days he sleeps until Gunner brings his friend Allen over to help his son. Allen figures out that Billy's story must be true. As such go goes into space to find him as Captain Atom. Billy had talked about the dark side of the moon in great detail giving Captain Atom a place to start. Captain Atom ends up finding Billy and convinces Billy not to leave home for so long.

Victory for Venus
name: The Little Wanderer ; Victory for Venus

description:
Sgt. Howitzer orders YOU to join the battle against the Evil Popcon in ‘Gunheadz’, debuting this week in 2000 AD Prog 1830! Created by TC Eglington and Boo Cook (Elephant Men), ‘Gunheadz’ is the latest Tharg’s 3riller to overload your Thrill receivers!

Also in this Prog: there’s trouble brewing amongst the recently-exiled Sov population in Judge Dredd: The Forsaken; burger me, it’s getting hairy in Dandridge: The Copper Conspiracy; the owl and the pussycat may have gone to see, but what’s Stickleback doing in a sewer in Number of the Beast; and it’s the battle of the planets in Zombo: Planet Zombo but will it be Earth or the Death Planet that is victorious?

There's a special retro cover this prog, sporting the very first 2000 AD logo.

Cover: Boo Cook (Tharg's 3rillers)

  • Droid Life (Cat Sullivan)
  • Judge Dredd - The Forsaken (part 1: Kessler) (Michael Carroll - PJ Holden)
  • Tharg's 3rillers - Gunheadz (part 1) (TC Eglington - Boo Cook)
  • Dandridge - The Copper Conspiracy (part 7) (Alec Worley - Warren Pleece)
  • Stickleback - Number of the Beast (part 7) (Ian Edginton - D'Israeli)
  • Zombo - Planet Zombo (part 6) (Al Ewing - Henry Flint)
